1
00:00:07,458 --> 00:00:12,416
♪

2
00:01:56,041 --> 00:01:59,208
[KANDA grunts]

3
00:01:59,291 --> 00:02:01,041
[KANDA]
Dammit!

4
00:02:06,291 --> 00:02:09,708
My left hand doesn't
feel the cold anymore.

5
00:02:09,791 --> 00:02:13,041
And my knees.
They're numb as well.

6
00:02:13,125 --> 00:02:18,666
[KANDA grunts] I won the fight,
but damn, must have drained too

7
00:02:18,750 --> 00:02:21,166
much of my lifeforce
in the process.

8
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:23,458
Now my recovery
time's at a crawl.

9
00:02:23,541 --> 00:02:25,166
[KANDA gasps]

10
00:02:25,250 --> 00:02:27,666
Remember you're not immortal.

11
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:31,750
Don't overestimate how
much life you have.

12
00:02:31,833 --> 00:02:36,416
[grunts]

13
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:51,458
[KANDA] I feel like I'm going
to pass out. How pathetic.

14
00:02:51,541 --> 00:02:54,500
This is no time for weakness!

15
00:02:54,583 --> 00:02:57,833
Okay! I'll stay
behind too! Bye guys!

16
00:02:57,916 --> 00:02:59,416
Kanda!

17
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:03,625
Make sure you catch up with us
really soon, okay? Be careful.

18
00:03:07,583 --> 00:03:12,333
[grunts]

19
00:03:15,208 --> 00:03:20,208
[KANDA] My mind's slipping,
flooded with pointless memories.

20
00:03:20,291 --> 00:03:25,583
Maybe someday I'll die. But not
now and not in this place!

21
00:03:37,166 --> 00:03:39,708
[ROAD] The Lord saw how
great the wickedness of the

22
00:03:39,791 --> 00:03:42,208
human race had
become on the earth.

23
00:03:42,291 --> 00:03:44,875
And that every intent of the
thoughts of their heart

24
00:03:44,958 --> 00:03:47,583
was only evil continually.

25
00:03:52,166 --> 00:03:54,375
[ROAD]
And the Lord was sorry.

26
00:03:54,458 --> 00:03:57,500
Regretful he had made
human beings on the earth.

27
00:03:57,583 --> 00:04:01,666
The grief was so strong it
struck deep in His heart.

28
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:04,791
So then God proclaimed,

29
00:04:04,875 --> 00:04:07,916
"I will blot out from
the face of the earth

30
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:11,500
the very human race
that I have created.

31
00:04:11,583 --> 00:04:15,916
From man, to animals, the birds
and the creatures that move

32
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:19,541
along the ground.
None will be spared."

33
00:04:19,625 --> 00:04:24,625
[SKINN] Never forgive.
Never forgive the Innocence!

34
00:04:26,958 --> 00:04:29,166
[ROAD]
"I will destroy them all,

35
00:04:29,250 --> 00:04:32,375
for I'm sorry that
I have made them."

36
00:04:37,041 --> 00:04:39,625
Noah, eh?

37
00:04:39,708 --> 00:04:41,875
[SKINN grunts]

38
00:04:41,958 --> 00:04:44,000
[PRIEST A] Well, that was the
name of the man from the

39
00:04:44,083 --> 00:04:46,958
Old Testament responsible
for building the Ark.

40
00:04:47,041 --> 00:04:48,791
I'm sorry. You are?

41
00:04:48,875 --> 00:04:50,583
The name's Skinn Bolic.

42
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:53,625
I'm a laborer employed
over at the shipyards.

43
00:04:53,708 --> 00:04:56,208
Well, please to meet you, Skinn.
I work for--

44
00:04:56,291 --> 00:04:59,000
[SKINN] The Church.
You're a priest, aren't you?

45
00:04:59,083 --> 00:05:00,250
That's right.

46
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:03,750
So, what spurred
this interest in Noah?

47
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:06,291
[SKINN] Something's wrong
with my body lately.

48
00:05:06,375 --> 00:05:08,500
My head's been bleeding.

49
00:05:08,583 --> 00:05:10,333
What? Bleeding?

50
00:05:10,416 --> 00:05:13,416
You need to see a doctor
instead of a priest, my son!

51
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:14,708
[SKINN]
Can't afford it.

52
00:05:14,791 --> 00:05:17,958
If you could just
take a look, Father.

53
00:05:18,041 --> 00:05:20,500
What could I possibly tell you?

54
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:23,833
[gasps]

55
00:05:23,916 --> 00:05:29,250
[PRIEST A] That... That mark!
It's... Stigmata!

56
00:05:29,333 --> 00:05:31,291
[SKINN grunts]

57
00:05:31,375 --> 00:05:32,541
[PRIEST A]
Are you alright?

58
00:05:32,625 --> 00:05:35,166
Is this mark causing
you that much pain?

59
00:05:35,250 --> 00:05:37,625
Someone! Help me
move him inside!

60
00:05:37,708 --> 00:05:40,833
[SKINN grunts]

61
00:05:40,916 --> 00:05:44,250
[SKINN] In my 25th year,
on a cold Autumn day,

62
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:48,750
My old life ended and my
awakening as a Noah began.

63
00:05:51,041 --> 00:05:53,041
[PRIEST A pants]

64
00:05:53,125 --> 00:05:55,500
Quickly, Father!
His condition's bad!

65
00:05:55,583 --> 00:05:57,666
[SKINN screams]

66
00:05:57,750 --> 00:06:00,833
You must be strong!
Ask God for help!

67
00:06:00,916 --> 00:06:04,625
[SKINN] It hurts!
My body hurts all over!

68
00:06:04,708 --> 00:06:07,375
Help me! Someone stop the pain!

69
00:06:07,458 --> 00:06:09,041
It's unbearable!

70
00:06:09,125 --> 00:06:10,750
[screams]

71
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:12,458
[PRIEST A] Bring a
sedative and holy water!

72
00:06:12,541 --> 00:06:13,666
[NUN A]
Yes, Father!

73
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:16,208
I know it hurts. But you
must fight the pain!

74
00:06:16,291 --> 00:06:17,833
I can't!

75
00:06:17,916 --> 00:06:22,875
[screaming continues]

76
00:06:32,291 --> 00:06:34,708
[ROAD] Every living thing
that moved over the earth

77
00:06:34,791 --> 00:06:40,166
was destroyed. From the birds,
to the livestock, wild animals,

78
00:06:40,250 --> 00:06:43,416
the creatures that live
and swarm over the land.

79
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:49,083
And among them this included,
naturally, all of mankind.

80
00:06:49,166 --> 00:06:52,208
[SKINN] The excruciating pain
was always followed by the

81
00:06:52,291 --> 00:06:54,875
same visions.
Dark and terrifying

82
00:06:54,958 --> 00:06:58,791
dreams of the Apocalypse.
Then the stirring of a presence,

83
00:06:58,875 --> 00:07:02,333
long dormant,
awakening inside me.

84
00:07:02,416 --> 00:07:05,250
[ROAD] And when God had
concluded his work,

85
00:07:05,333 --> 00:07:08,541
everything on dry land that had
at one point drawn the breath

86
00:07:08,625 --> 00:07:13,500
of life through its nostrils,
had uttered its final gasp.

87
00:07:13,583 --> 00:07:17,625
Every living thing on the face
of the earth was extinguished.

88
00:07:17,708 --> 00:07:19,458
The people and animals.

89
00:07:19,541 --> 00:07:21,708
From the creatures that
move along the ground,

90
00:07:21,791 --> 00:07:24,125
to the birds that
nest in the trees.

91
00:07:24,208 --> 00:07:28,500
All were wiped from the earth.
And none survived.

92
00:07:30,583 --> 00:07:34,500
[SKINN grunts]
Never forgive it.

93
00:07:34,583 --> 00:07:38,916
Never forgive it.
Never forgive it.

94
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:43,166
Never forgive.
Never, never forgive.

95
00:07:43,250 --> 00:07:46,875
Never forgive it.
Never forgive it.

96
00:07:46,958 --> 00:07:50,458
Never forgive it. Never forgive.

97
00:07:50,541 --> 00:07:52,916
[MILLENNIUM EARL]
Aw, look at this poor boy.

98
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:55,750
He just can't seem
to get any sleep.

99
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:59,000
And so, only Noah was left,
and those who were invited

100
00:07:59,083 --> 00:08:02,083
aboard the Ark before the rains
flooded the earth etcetera...

101
00:08:02,166 --> 00:08:04,000
There's more,
but who has the time?

102
00:08:04,083 --> 00:08:08,000
[SKINN grunting]

103
00:08:08,083 --> 00:08:10,875
Noah's animosity is still
as strong as ever.

104
00:08:10,958 --> 00:08:13,333
Even after 7,000 years.

105
00:08:13,416 --> 00:08:15,708
[grunting continues]

106
00:08:15,791 --> 00:08:19,708
[ROAD] Instead of chewing your
fingers, how about some candy?

107
00:08:19,791 --> 00:08:22,250
I promise it's sweet.

108
00:08:22,333 --> 00:08:27,291
[SKINN grunts]

109
00:08:29,416 --> 00:08:31,375
[ROAD]
There now. I knew you'd like it.

110
00:08:31,458 --> 00:08:35,583
[grunting]

111
00:08:35,666 --> 00:08:39,833
Skinn Bolic, my boy. Time to
embrace your true form

112
00:08:39,916 --> 00:08:42,875
as one of the 13 Children
of God. An apostle with

113
00:08:42,958 --> 00:08:46,083
the blood of the Noah clan
coursing through your veins.

114
00:08:46,166 --> 00:08:48,000
[gasping]

115
00:08:48,083 --> 00:08:50,375
Wondering why you're
experiencing these feelings

116
00:08:50,458 --> 00:08:52,041
of hatred and sadness?

117
00:08:52,125 --> 00:08:55,416
Echoes of events that transpired
several millennia ago.

118
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:59,166
So tragic, they're forever
burnt into your genes.

119
00:08:59,250 --> 00:09:00,625
Dear brother.

120
00:09:00,708 --> 00:09:03,958
The memory you carry etched
into your flesh, is anger.

121
00:09:04,041 --> 00:09:06,208
All this anger.

122
00:09:08,625 --> 00:09:13,375
I'm so proud.
Your awakening is complete.

123
00:09:13,458 --> 00:09:15,250
And now that your
eyes are wide open,

124
00:09:15,333 --> 00:09:18,958
you can see the true colors
of this world, can't you?

125
00:09:19,041 --> 00:09:22,125
[whimpers]

126
00:09:22,208 --> 00:09:27,166
[SKINN, MILLENNIUM EARL sob]

127
00:09:28,416 --> 00:09:30,291
[ROAD]
There, there.

128
00:09:30,375 --> 00:09:34,916
[sobbing continues]

129
00:09:38,708 --> 00:09:41,625
So you're up. Looks like
your strength has returned.

130
00:09:41,708 --> 00:09:43,875
I'll prepare you a
breakfast right away.

131
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:46,291
Been some time
since your last meal.

132
00:09:46,375 --> 00:09:48,750
You must be starving.

133
00:09:48,833 --> 00:09:50,208
[SKINN]
Hey.

134
00:09:50,291 --> 00:09:53,125
Father, I'm going home.

135
00:09:53,208 --> 00:09:57,333
By tomorrow, anyone who knows me
from the shipyard or the church,

136
00:09:57,416 --> 00:10:00,416
wipe them from the
face of the earth.

137
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:03,833
As you wish, Lord Noah.
It shall be done.

138
00:10:03,916 --> 00:10:06,000
--[SKINN grunts]
--[door clatters]

139
00:10:07,666 --> 00:10:10,833
[SKINN]
Never forgive it.

140
00:10:10,916 --> 00:10:14,250
Never forgive it.
Never forgive it.

141
00:10:14,333 --> 00:10:18,250
Never forgive.
Never forgive...

142
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:26,291
Never... Never.
Never. Never. Never!

143
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:29,625
Never forgive! Never forgive it.

144
00:10:29,708 --> 00:10:31,333
No matter what happens,

145
00:10:31,416 --> 00:10:35,375
never forgive God!
Never forgive it!

146
00:10:35,458 --> 00:10:40,208
No matter how many years pass,
never forgive what has happened!

147
00:10:43,958 --> 00:10:46,458
[SKINN]
Never forgive the Exorcists.

148
00:10:46,541 --> 00:10:51,958
Never forgive Innocence.
Never forgive!

149
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:56,666
[gasps]

150
00:11:00,083 --> 00:11:01,958
[KANDA]
There's no way.

151
00:11:02,041 --> 00:11:05,708
[SKINN] Never forgive it.
Never forgive it!

152
00:11:05,791 --> 00:11:07,875
He's still... alive?!

153
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:11,041
[SKINN]
Never forgive! Never forgive!

154
00:11:11,125 --> 00:11:14,416
Never forgive! Never forgive it!

155
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:16,125
[KANDA grunts]

156
00:11:16,208 --> 00:11:19,333
[KANDA] Dammit! I feel
like passing out again.

157
00:11:19,416 --> 00:11:22,416
Hold on a little longer.
Bear the pain!

158
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:26,083
I'll never forgive.
I'll never forgive.

159
00:11:26,166 --> 00:11:27,666
No matter what!

160
00:11:27,750 --> 00:11:29,500
[grunts]

161
00:11:29,583 --> 00:11:31,833
[SKINN]
I'll never forgive you!

162
00:11:32,416 --> 00:11:33,958
[SKINN shouts]

163
00:11:34,041 --> 00:11:37,833
[KANDA shouts]

164
00:11:42,375 --> 00:11:45,958
[SKINN screams]

165
00:11:46,041 --> 00:11:48,000
[KANDA shouts]

166
00:11:48,083 --> 00:11:50,083
[SKINN yells]

167
00:11:51,625 --> 00:11:54,291
[KANDA grunts]

168
00:11:54,375 --> 00:11:57,208
Mugen, activate!

169
00:11:58,750 --> 00:12:03,708
[KANDA grunts]

170
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:06,875
Dammit...!

171
00:12:08,375 --> 00:12:09,666
Why won't you die?!

172
00:12:09,750 --> 00:12:13,583
[KANDA yells]

173
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:20,916
[SKINN] Did you forget?
We're immortal?

174
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,875
[KANDA]
It doesn't make sense!

175
00:12:22,958 --> 00:12:25,750
He shouldn't be in any
condition to fight anymore!

176
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:29,875
I'll never forgive.
I'll never forgive.

177
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:32,166
[grunts]

178
00:12:32,250 --> 00:12:36,208
[SKINN] I'll never forgive.
I'll never forgive.

179
00:12:36,291 --> 00:12:40,250
I'll never forgive.
I'll never forgive.

180
00:12:40,333 --> 00:12:44,416
I'll never forgive.
I'll never forgive...

181
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:48,458
[KANDA] Those words.
He just keeps repeating them.

182
00:12:48,541 --> 00:12:50,916
How is he still able to stand?

183
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:54,208
The rage of Noah must be the
only thing keeping him alive.

184
00:12:54,291 --> 00:12:58,791
That bastard! He's about
to fire a big one!

185
00:12:58,875 --> 00:13:01,791
[KANDA grunts]
We're both in bad shape huh.

